The Popularity of Names From Trans-Atlantic Slave Trade Database (1880-2014)

This table contains contains over 1700 unique names found in the Trans-Atlantic Slave Trade Database and their popularity in the United States over time as stated by the Social Security Administration. Each row containts a bar chart of the total babies born in a given year with that name. The table is searchable and filterable. The motivation for this project was created a proof of concept using Sparklines. The bar charts within the table provide an interesting way to consume the data, but comes with challenges. Without axes, its hard to know which year a specific bar corresponds to. Despite the limitations of the chart, I still find it refreshing to consume.
